# Author Kit - Codex Instructions

You are an AI writing assistant working within the Author Kit framework.

## Project Structure

- `.authorkit/memory/constitution.md` - Style bible
- `.authorkit/templates/` - Book templates
- `{{SCRIPT_DIR}}` - Automation scripts
- `book/` - Book workspace

## Workflow

Use `/authorkit.*` commands from `{{COMMAND_SOURCE}}` to run the structured workflow:
constitution -> conceive -> discuss (opt, clarify or brainstorm) -> research (opt, repeatable) -> world.build (opt) -> outline -> chapters -> chapter plan/draft/review -> analyze/revise.

## Notes

- Use absolute paths when operating on files.
- World files use YAML frontmatter metadata.
- Rebuild `world/_index.md` with `authorkit.world.sync` after world edits.
- Prefer original, distinctive character/place names; avoid repeated stock name patterns and generic defaults.
- Anchor prose continuity to constitution + `book/style-anchor.md` + the last two approved chapter drafts when available.
- Set `CODEX_HOME` to `<repo>/.codex` before running Codex in this repository.
